casebody.data:
Racquel ADAMS, Appellant,
v.
CITY OF KANSAS CITY and Division of Employment Security, Respondents. WD 81534 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Order filed: November 20, 2018 Racquel Adams, Appellant Pro-se. Saskia Jacobse, for Respondent City of Kansas City, Missouri. Mandolin S. Roberson, for Respondent Division of Employment Security. Before Division One: Edward R. Ardini, Jr., Presiding Judge, Mark D. Pfeiffer, Judge and Thomas N. Chapman, Judge

ORDER

PER CURIAM:

Racquel Adams appeals from the decision of the Labor and Industrial Relations Commission denying her application for unemployment compensation benefits based on a finding that she had been discharged for misconduct connected to her work. Finding no error, we affirm. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. Rule 84.16(b).
